Blocks.childText: No. 41. I AM WAITING. Words and Music by J. L. ORR. 1. I am wait - ing, I am wait - ing, Where the bil - lows loud - ly roar; 2. I am wait - ing, I am wait - ing, Till the night has passed a - way; 3. I am wait - ing, I am wait - ing, Where life's shadows thick-ly fall I am long-ing, am long - ing To be tak en safe - ly o'er. am watching, am watch-ing For the break-ing of the day. I am list'ning, am list'ning For my Sav-ior's gen-tle call. CHORUS. Wait - ing for my an gel boat-man, Who will row me o'er the tide, To the friends who wait to greet me On the far off oth - er side. From the "Silver Cymbal," by per. (45)
